[thinking] I'm considering whether JSON supports interpolating values into field names only if the key isn't quoted. But what about quoted interpolation, like `{ "prefix-$id": 1 }`? My guess is that it probably doesn't allow splicing into JSON strings because it seems to use placeholders instead. I need to look into how the macro works. It looks for placeholders in the string and uses asJson/asKey for replacement. I wonder if interpolated strings are supported, such as `json""""Hello, $name""""` producing "Hello, [encoded?]." I'll need to check the source for more information.
